From Ed Breen Subject DICTA Australian Pattern Recognition Society CALL FOR PAPERS DICTA Conference on DIGITAL IMAGING COMPUTING TECHNIQUES AND APPLICATIONS Location Macquarie Theatre Macquarie University Sydney Date December DICTA is the second biennial national conference of the Australian Pattern Recognition This event will provide an opportunity for any persons with an interest in computer vision digital image processing analysis and other aspects of pattern recognition to become informed about contemporary developments in the area to exchange ideas to establish contacts and to share details of their own work with The Following invited speakers will provide specialised presentations Prof Gabor Herman University of Pennsylvania on Medical Hodgson Massey University New Zealand on Computer Dominique Juelin Centre de Morphologie Mathematique Paris on Mathematical John Richards Defence Force Academy Canberra on Remote Phillip Robertson CSIRO Division of Information Technology Canberra on Interactive The conference will concentrate on but is not limited to the following areas of image processing Computer Vision and Object Recognition Motion Analysis Morphology Medical Imaging Fuzzy logic and Neural Networks Image Coding Machine Vision and Robotics Enhancement and Restoration Enhancement and Restoration Visualisation Industrial Applications Software and Hardware Tools Papers are sought for presentation at the conference and publication in the conference Submission for peer review should consist of an extended abstract of words of doubled spaced text summarizing the technical aspects of the paper and any results that will be Final papers should be limited to no more than pages of text and illustrations in camera ready Four copies of the abstract should be sent to DICTA C Tony Adriaansen CSIRO Division of Wool Technology PO Box Ryde NSW Australia IMPORTANT DATES Abstract due June Acceptance notified August Final paper due October SOCIAL PROGRAM The conference dinner will